PARAGRAPH.#text: PPG Industries Inc. PPG declared a force majeure for some of its chemical products as the result of a fire at a Louisiana plant Monday. A force majeure is declared when a company is unable to fulfill its contractual obligations to deliver products due to circumstances beyond its control. The supplier of paints, chemicals and other products said the move affects shipments of vinyl chloride monomer manufactured at the Louisiana chemicals plant and liquid caustic soda produced companywide. The fire resulted in the shutdown of the vinyl chloride monomer unit and reduced chlor-alkali operating rates.

Headlines.Author: Patrick McGee
Headlines.Headline: Top-Quality Corporate Bonds Rally as a Preferred 'Safe Haven'

PARAGRAPH.#text: Investment returns on highly rated corporate bonds are outpacing their lower-rated peers this month as investors look for safe-haven alternatives to Treasurys. Bank of America Merill Lynch Research notes that spreads on AA-rated bonds declined by 25% in July, versus 13% for A-rated and 8% for BBB-rated debt. Spreads measure the extra yield premium these corporate bonds pay investors, compared with yields on comparable Treasury securities. Since bond yields move inversely to prices, the bigger decline for top-rated bonds indicates robust demand for safer forms of debt.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Top-Quality Corporate Bonds Rally as a Preferred 'Safe Haven'

PARAGRAPH.#text: -- Akzo Nobel abandons full-year outlook after quarterly profits slide -- Dutch group now gives no detailed full-year guidance -- Launches EUR500 million cost savings plan (Rewrites throughout.) AMSTERDAM (Dow Jones)--Dutch chemical company Akzo Nobel NV (AKZA.AE) Thursday abandoned its full-year outlook and launched a wide-ranging cost saving program to safeguard its mid-term financial targets as profit dropped amid a weakening global economy. The world's biggest paint maker, which had already lowered earnings expectations in June due to higher costs, said net profit fell 37% to EUR149 million despite a 4.8% rise in revenue to EUR4.05 billion as higher prices for raw materials like pigments and oil-related resins and solvents continued to dent profits.

    65 percent increase from the January total. Assets for the whole fund industry, including

contaminants, stirring up painful emotions between the town and the company
